    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>Welcome to the Budget Claims System. This application is designed to help you manage vehicle claims efficiently. Below, you will find detailed guides and instructions for using various features of the system.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Getting Started</h2>
            <h3>Login</h3>
            <p>To access the system, you need to log in with your credentials. If you do not have an account, please contact your administrator.</p>
            <h3>Dashboard</h3>
            <p>The dashboard provides an overview of key metrics and analytics, such as the number of claims processed, open vs. closed claims, average resolution time, etc. This helps management track performance and identify areas for improvement.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Managing Claims</h2>
            <h3>Adding a New Claim</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to the "Claims" page.</li>
                <li>Click on the "Add Claim" button.</li>
                <li>Fill in the required fields: MVA, Customer Name, Description, and Status.</li>
                <li>If necessary, upload relevant files.</li>
                <li>Click "Submit" to save the new claim.</li>
            </ol>
            <h3>Editing an Existing Claim</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to the "Claims" page.</li>
                <li>Click on the claim you wish to edit.</li>
                <li>Update the necessary fields and upload any additional files if needed.</li>
                <li>Click "Save" to update the claim.</li>
            </ol>
            <h3>Searching and Filtering Claims</h3>
            <p>Use the search form on the "Claims" page to filter claims based on various criteria, including MVA, Customer Name, Status, and Date Range. This helps you quickly find specific claims.</p>
            <h3>Deleting a Claim</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to the "Claims" page.</li>
                <li>Click on the claim you wish to delete.</li>
                <li>Click the "Delete" button to remove the claim from the system.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Notifications</h2>
            <p>The system sends email notifications for various events, such as:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>New claim created</li>
                <li>Claim status updated</li>
                <li>Reminders for pending tasks</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Ensure your email settings are configured correctly to receive notifications.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Activity Logging</h2>
            <p>The system tracks user activities, such as logins, claim creations, edits, and deletions. This helps in auditing and understanding user behavior within the application. Activity logs can be viewed by administrators for security and auditing purposes.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>File Versioning</h2>
            <p>When editing a claim, the system saves a version of the claim before making updates. This maintains a history of changes and allows you to revert to previous versions if needed.</p>
            <h3>Viewing Claim Versions</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to the claim you wish to view.</li>
                <li>Click on the "Versions" tab to see the history of changes made to the claim.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)</h2>
            <p>The system uses role-based access control to manage user permissions. There are three roles:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Admin</strong>: Full access to all features, including user management and activity logs.</li>
                <li><strong>Manager</strong>: Access to most features, including claim management and dashboard analytics, but limited access to user management.</li>
                <li><strong>Employee</strong>: Limited access to view and manage claims.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Generating Reports</h2>
            <p>Generate reports in CSV, Excel, or PDF formats to analyze and share data.</p>
            <h3>Creating a Report</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to the "Reports" page.</li>
                <li>Select the report type and format.</li>
                <li>Choose the data fields and apply any filters.</li>
                <li>Click "Generate Report" to download the file.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>API Access</h2>
            <p>The system provides API endpoints for key functionalities, allowing other applications to interact with the Budget Claims System. API documentation is available for developers to integrate with third-party services.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Data Import/Export</h2>
            <p>Import data from external sources and export data to various formats to facilitate data migration and sharing.</p>
            <h3>Importing Data</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to the "Data Import" page.</li>
                <li>Upload the file containing the data.</li>
                <li>Map the fields to the system's database structure.</li>
                <li>Click "Import" to upload the data.</li>
            </ol>
            <h3>Exporting Data</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to the "Data Export" page.</li>
                <li>Select the data fields and apply any filters.</li>
                <li>Choose the format (CSV, Excel, PDF).</li>
                <li>Click "Export" to download the file.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>User Feedback System</h2>
            <p>Report issues, suggest features, and provide general feedback to help improve the system.</p>
            <h3>Submitting Feedback</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to the "Feedback" page.</li>
                <li>Fill in the feedback form with your comments and suggestions.</li>
                <li>Click "Submit" to send your feedback to the system administrators.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Support</h2>
            <p>If you need further assistance, please contact our support team at <a href="mailto:support@budgetclaims.com">support@budgetclaims.com</a>.</p>
        </section>
    </main>
